From: Shin (LiteLLM agent)
Subject: [PATCH] fix(proxy/auth): honour general_settings.user_api_key_cache_ttl for management-object cache writes (LIT-3338)

Customer report (NVIDIA, Pylon #4339): `general_settings.user_api_key_cache_ttl: 300`
is ignored; cache entries still expire after 60s.

Root cause: `_cache_management_object()` and several auth-checks call sites
write to `user_api_key_cache.async_set_cache(..., ttl=DEFAULT_MANAGEMENT_OBJECT_IN_MEMORY_CACHE_TTL)`.
The explicit ttl override always wins over the cache's `default_in_memory_ttl`
that `proxy_server.py` updates from `general_settings.user_api_key_cache_ttl`.

Fix: read `user_api_key_cache.default_in_memory_ttl` at write time (with the
constant as a fallback for bare cache instances in tests). The cache's
`default_in_memory_ttl` is initialised to 60s at startup and overridden by
`general_settings.user_api_key_cache_ttl` when configured.

---
 litellm/proxy/auth/auth_checks.py                 | 41 ++++++++--
 tests/test_litellm/proxy/auth/test_auth_checks.py | 95 +++++++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 129 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

